This article is a speech given by the Second Lady of the United States, Debbie Dingell, at the Sylvester Cancer Center in Broward County, Florida. Dingell praises the courage of a congresswoman who has battled cancer and is now helping other survivors. She emphasizes the importance of community and collaboration in the fight against cancer and mentions the Cancer Moonshot initiative, which aims to transform cancer care and save lives. Dingell encourages individuals to prioritize their health by getting necessary screenings, particularly mammograms. She concludes by expressing gratitude to the audience for their dedication to fighting cancer.